The paper discusses the h-index, which is a measure of research impact, and applies the non-parametric bootstrap technique to construct confidence intervals for the h-index for different fields of research. This methodology is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), statistics (cs.ST), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CY).
